SIMPLE: triphthong
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triphthong
<hw>Triph"thong</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>-phthong</ets>, as in <ets>diphthong</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>triphthonque</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Orthoepy)</fld> <def>A
combination of three vowel sounds in a single syllable, forming a simple
or compound sound; also, a union of three vowel characters, representing
together a single sound; a trigraph; <as>as, <ex>eye</ex>, <ex>-ieu</ex>
in <ex>adieu</ex>, <ex>-eau</ex> in <ex>beau</ex>, are examples of
<ex>triphthongs</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triphthongal</ent>⟦br⟧
